      • fromPackage

        public static <DBTYPE extends ChronoDBInternal> MigrationChain<DBTYPE> fromPackage(java.lang.String qualifiedPackageName)
        Description copied from interface: MigrationChain
        Creates a new MigrationChain from the given Java package name.

        This method will scan all classes in the package, looking for classes that extend ChronosMigration and have an @Migration annotation.

        The following conditions apply on the ChronosMigration classes:

        • The classes must be top-level classes, i.e. they must not be nested.
        • The classes must implement ChronosMigration.
        • The classes must be annotated with @Migration (directly; inheriting this annotation is not supported).
        • The classes must have a default constructor.
        • The version ranges given by the @Migration interfaces must not intersect.
        Specified by:
        fromPackage in interface MigrationChain<DBTYPE extends ChronoDBInternal>
        Parameters:
        qualifiedPackageName - The fully qualified name of the java package to scan. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        The migration chain of classes found in the given package. Never null, may be empty.
